result.name: register-of-architects
result.notes: The Architects Registration Board (ARB) is the body set up by Parliament as the independent UK regulator of architects. Anyone who describes themself as an architect must be on the Register of Architects

organization.name: architects-registration-board
organization.title: Architects Registration Board
organization.description:
The Architects Registration Board (ARB) regulates the architects’ profession in the UK to ensure that good standards of conduct and practice are consistently maintained.

ARB is a public corporation of the Department for Communities and Local Government

http://www.arb.org.uk
